{
  "stem": "19690.2",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 305.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "At one point, we got to talking to one of them later in the day and he was complaining he hadn't had any sleep in over 24 hours.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "We didn't really feel sorry for him, but we realized that this was an operation that had started long before we were woken up.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Anyway, we stayed there overnight.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Next morning, we were loaded in trains.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "These were regular passenger trains.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And they started leaving one at a time.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "At one point, we were stopped on a railroad terminal and another train was added to ours and we found out that it was people from Wurms and Mainz that were on another train that was added to our train.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And then the train started to move out into the occupied French area, so we [? knew were in ?] France.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Oh, we found out earlier that we were going to France because they changed our German money, what we had.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "We were allowed to take 100 marks with us.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "They changed the 100 marks into French money, 100 marks per person.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And then we were on this train going through all these towns.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "Every time the train stopped, the guards were out.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "You could not get off the train for any reason.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "Then on the second day, we woke up in the morning and there were no guards and we realized that we were in the unoccupied area of France, also known as Vichy France.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And the train kept going.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "It was not considered a priority train, so every time a freight train came along, it was sidetracked to let the freight through.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "So it was a very slow progress.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We wound up after three days, on the 25th of October, in a town called [INAUDIBLE] in southern France.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
